<TITLE> Police recover 2 girls' bodies in Meherpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Meherpur, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Police recovered the bodies of two girls from a field at Jadabpur village in Buripota union, Meherpur, less than 24 hours apart on Friday and Saturday. The bodies were discovered near the site of a month-long bingo fest, Rabiul Islam, Meherpur police chief said. He said, "Both the deceased were wearing salwar kameez. Their identities and cause of death could not be ascertained yet." He guessed that the bodies had been buried for about three days. The police also confirmed that neither of the dead girls hailed from Meherpur. Syed Morshed, Meherpur executive magistrate, was present during exhumation of the bodies. bdn
